<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-112] Maven jetty plugin has been relocated</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-112</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Seen when building taste-web in the 0.1 release candidate and in the current Mahout trunk:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Downloading:
http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/mortbay/jetty/maven-jetty-plugin/7.0.0.pre5/maven-jetty-plugin-7.0.0.pre5.jar
[INFO] ------------------------------------------------------------------------
[ERROR] BUILD FAILURE
[INFO] ------------------------------------------------------------------------
[INFO] A required plugin was not found: Plugin could not be found - check that the goal name is correct:
Unable to download the artifact from any repository
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Jetty plugin has been relocated from maven-jetty-plugin to jetty-maven-plugin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following change solves the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Index: taste-web/pom.xml
===================================================================
--- taste-web/pom.xml	(Revision 760032)
+++ taste-web/pom.xml	(Arbeitskopie)
@@ -82,7 +82,7 @@
 
       &amp;lt;plugin&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;org.mortbay.jetty&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;
-        &amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;maven-jetty-plugin&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;
+        &amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;jetty-maven-plugin&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;
           &amp;lt;webApp&amp;gt;${project.build.directory}/${project.artifactId}-${project.version}.war&amp;lt;/webApp&amp;gt;
         &amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
